      "side": 1,
      "message": "This doesn\u0027t feel right to me. It feels/reads like we have a special mechanism when it comes to CUE that contains `@inject` attributes, outside of the existing unification mechanism. I was expecting this to read:\n\n```\nconfig: *\"default\" | _ @inject(name\u003d\"example.com/myapp/config\")\n```\n\nI assume this was a typo, not least because of the text that follows, but also because there is no explanation of why this separate default mechanism would be required.\n\nIndeed I think this test (which passes) confirms this must be a typo:\n\n```\nfunc TestInjectUnifyDefault(t *testing.T) {\n\tj :\u003d cuecontext.NewInjector()\n\tj.AllowAll()\n\tctx :\u003d cuecontext.New(cuecontext.Inject(j))\n\n\tj.Register(\"example.com/foo\", ctx.CompileString(`\"injected\"`))\n\n\tv :\u003d ctx.CompileString(`\n\t\t@extern(inject)\n\n\t\tpackage foo\n\n\t\tx: \"default\" @inject(name\u003d\"example.com/foo\")\n\t`)\n\tqt.Assert(t, qt.IsNotNil(v.Err()))\n\tqt.Assert(t, qt.ErrorMatches(v.Err(), `.*conflicting values \"injected\" and \"default\"`))\n}\n```\n\nAnd this test confirm that my version as written is what was intended:\n\n```\nfunc TestInjectUnifyProperDefault(t *testing.T) {\n\tj :\u003d cuecontext.NewInjector()\n\tj.AllowAll()\n\tctx :\u003d cuecontext.New(cuecontext.Inject(j))\n\n\tj.Register(\"example.com/foo\", ctx.CompileString(`\"injected\"`))\n\n\tv :\u003d ctx.CompileString(`\n\t\t@extern(inject)\n\n\t\tpackage foo\n\n\t\tx: *\"default\" | _ @inject(name\u003d\"example.com/foo\")\n\t\ty: *\"default\" | _ @inject(name\u003d\"example.com/bar\")\n\t`)\n\tqt.Assert(t, qt.IsNil(v.Err()))\n\tx :\u003d v.LookupPath(cue.ParsePath(\"x\"))\n\ty :\u003d v.LookupPath(cue.ParsePath(\"y\"))\n\tgotx, errx :\u003d x.String()\n\tgoty, erry :\u003d y.String()\n\tqt.Assert(t, qt.IsNil(errx))\n\tqt.Assert(t, qt.IsNil(erry))\n\tqt.Assert(t, qt.Equals(gotx, \"injected\"))\n\tqt.Assert(t, qt.Equals(goty, \"default\"))\n}\n```\n\nSome tangentially, I will not that on further thinking the points in https://github.com/cue-lang/cue/issues/3296 a very relevant here. But that\u0027s a separate discussion.",
      "revId": "6333e17303356f46eb5143e5d27212619c75a58d",
